<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,247]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis box="[199,335,151,176]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,151,176]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">Comments</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Collected quite close to the original site of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bagnall" authorityYear="1914" box="[831,954,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Physothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennatus">
<emphasis box="[831,954,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">antennatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, these two species are closely related. The new species is bicoloured, with the tergal sculpture particularly distinctive, the sculptured lines on the pronotum and metanotum much less closely spaced, and the major sensoria on the antennae more slender.
</paragraph>
